,Recommended,407230,21139917,"Posted: 11 February, 2016",all,Kohe,"Review Upon Legend Of Mysteria RPGWritten by Rias GremoryProsThis game isn't really my type of game, but I enjoyed playing the first couple of 'hours' of the game, I have seen not really any problems, there are not really many tips, so you will have to find your own, The art style is very dark and 'pixely' but I can see through that and enjoy the game play, the HUD is easy to use and extremely simple, like no joke. The game isn't all that fast paced, but it has small animal fights like pokemon, (seen in the trailer on steam store) of which I do feel is a bit cheap of them to do, but that is their game...ConsI was unable to get the feel of the game, even after playing like 16 hours of it. I found it hard to follow the story due to the lack of information on the steam store page, and really just all over the internet. I seemed to run really fast when going sideways as well, I noticed the fact that you can go faster going left or right on your keyboard than going forward or backwards (evening this out would make a heavy difference. Overall I did find a lot of the start to be a bit silly, and not really immersive, but I would still play the game.Overall ReviewGiving the fact that the game lacks in the immersive story telling, and the fact that it is just like a lot of other cheap basic RPG games, I would still find a way for me to play it, and have fun, whether this being hacking (Item mods) or possibly even messing with game files, I would be able to spend my time playing this sky view RPG game. I would not reccomend this game to those who hate story lacking games, but if you wish to try it, then feel free. There is not really much I can say about this game, as I have not really completed it.Extra InformationDeveloper(s):LabyrinthinePublisher(s):EQ GamesPlatform(s):WindowsRelease Date:October 9th 2015Source(s)Personal ExperienceSteam Store PageGoogleWritten for 11th Floor11th Floor Group"
