,Recommended,407230,30987061,Posted: 6 April,all,That Guy ☆VG☆,"Legend of Mysteria is an RPG Maker made RPG set as a prequel to another game in their series by the same author. Though it's made via RPG Maker, it has a different feel to it rather than the typical RPG maker made game for better and for worse.This game is about the main character Windir, whom you get accused of murder and have to prove you innocence. It's mainly about exploring your locations, talking to NPC's, gathering evidences, finding and using items to unlock new and previously locked rooms and area. It has an intruging story that kept me lingering and not much of a combat system (which isn't a minus), but has a very confusing and uninformative use of items to progress the story.At the start it's interesting enough to read all the documents and uncover clues to find out who framed you, but then it becomes a nightmare of finding objects and find where you are supposed to use them, some of which I had no idea how you where supposed to find out the solution without a walkthough.There is not nearly enough tips in the game as of how to use certain items, for example, how are you supposed to know Djinni is able to spy on people if you put its crystal in a nearby ""cup"" or ""bucket""? How are you supposed to know which object corresponds to which crystal in the corridor of elements to get the tome of elements? How are you supposed to know which documents you are supposed to use on different people to get to the next point in the game? There's a plethora of items to use and not much information to let you know when or where to use it and with whom.Pros:+ Windir's story, the plot is very good+ Crime investigation+ Combat system is very simplistic and not often used, which is nice for a investigation styled RPG+ Lack of a love story, it's short and abrupt which isn't very expectedCons:- Really hard puzzles & quests (time-consuming to find the correct person/place/object you're supposed to interact with and how)- A lot of backtrackingTL;DR:6.5/10For an RPG Maker made game it's very well done, one of the better RPG Maker games I've played, and I've played quite a few of them. It's mostly a criminal investigation style game with some rare instances where you have to use combat, mostly just interactions. Complicated use of items to progress the story so if you really wanna get this game done and over with fast (less than 10 hours) I'd strongly suggest using a guide.https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=533832171"
