,Recommended,407230,33798850,Posted: 25 July,all,YPRPG,"Legend of Mysteria is a prequel to Labyronia RPG, but the style of gameplay is very different. There are only a handful of battles (some of them quite difficult), and the game centers mostly around exploring, finding necessary items, and using them appropriately in the right locations to progress your way through the game. It's fun for the first hour or so (of a 6 hour game), but there are many things you have to discover, and they aren't always obvious. The remaining five hours are spent consulting the walkthrough at every turn.The premise of the story is that, after a leading wizard apparently is murdered, and you are implicated and imprisoned, you must disguise yourself and gather evidence to find the real culprit among 12 suspects. There is such a large cast of characters that it is difficult to keep track of the different stories of who's who and who did what, and unfortunately, this is crucial to figuring out which of the dozens of notes and diaries to use in front of which characters, which again, requires consultation with the walkthrough.Aside from a painful reliance on walkthroughs, there are few things to complain about. The game is rich in content, and the story, while too broad at first, wraps up nicely towards the end, and the ending itself is very satisfying. Overall, it's a fun game."
